 asymmetric downside risks associated with Samsung's competitive re-entry and the speculative nature of AI capex are not adequately compensated at this valuation.", "source": null, "title": "$MU: Passing on a Fairly Valued Supercycle with Asymmetric Downside", "url": "https://tickertothesis.com/mu-investment-memo-2026-02-05/"}, {"date": null, "snippet": "The article uses a research-note framework focused on business quality, earnings durability, valuation sensitivity, and downside risk rather than personalized investment advice.", "source": null, "title": "Micron's AI Memory Upcycle Is Strong, but Valuation Depends on DRAM ...", "url": "https://www.capitalsight.net/2026/04/micron-technology-mu-deep-dive.html"}, {"date": null, "snippet": "Micron's FY2026 Q2 delivered record results: $23.86B revenue (+196% YoY), Non-GAAP EPS of $12.20 beating its own guidance by 45%, and gross margin jumping from 56.8% to 75%. But a $25B+ capex plan, 81% Q3 gross margin guidance, and $58B+ in industry-wide capex spending make the cycle-peak debate unavoidable.", "source": null, "title": "Micron (MU) Q2 FY2026: $23.9B Record Revenue, 75% Gross Margin", "url": "https://momoview.com/blog/en/posts/micron-mu-fy2026-q2-earnings-record-revenue-hbm-capex-cycle-risk/"}, {"date": null, "snippet": "A major risk is the cyclical nature of semiconductors. The market is pricing in a peak, but the cycle could turn. Any sign of demand softening from hyperscalers or a ramp in supply from competitors could trigger a sharp correction. The recent pullback, despite blowout results, suggests investors are already weighing this vulnerability. The guidance reset has moved the goalposts, but it hasn't ...", "source": null, "title": "Micron's 81% Margin Guidance Sets Up High-Risk, High-Reward Trade as ...", "url": "https://www.ainvest.com/news/micron-81-margin-guidance-sets-high-risk-high-reward-trade-market-questions-sustainability-ai-powered-boom-2603/"}, {"date": null, "snippet": "MU's grade is Buy, with moderate downside risk (CVaR -15.5%), and quality metrics (net margin 41%, ROE 40%). Micron Technology Inc. (MU) trades at $1,133.99 with a valuation grade of Buy: a trailing P/E of 53.4x at a 67% premium to sector median, net margins of 41.5%, a DCF-implied intrinsic range of $413-$1,791 suggesting a -3% margin of ...", "source": null, "title": "Micron Technology Inc. (MU) Stock Analysis 2026: Buy Rating & DCF Valuation", "url": "https://alcapitaladvisory.com/research/equities/mu.html"}]}, "query": "MU downside risk competition margin valuation guidance concern latest", "step": "search_query_3_risk"}, {"output": [{"access_status": "ok", "as_of": "2026-06-29T08:37:00.140519+00:00", "canonical_url": "https://tickertothesis.com/mu-investment-memo-2026-02-05", "completed_at": "2026-06-29T08:37:16.655404+00:00", "content_hash": "14e210febd908d0d7a4d1fe739c7206ce615fc64dde4d8a433a5d9a852bc1f0b", "content_type": "text/html; charset=utf-8", "error": null, "ok": true, "paragraphs": ["$MU: Passing on a Fairly Valued Supercycle with Asymmetric Downside Home About Disclaimer Sign in Subscribe $MU: Passing on a Fairly Valued Supercycle with Asymmetric Downside 1.", "Executive Summary We recommend PASS on Micron Technology (MU) at its current price of ~$419.", "While we recognize Micron's superb operational execution, its temporary duopoly in the High Bandwidth Memory (HBM) market, and the powerful secular tailwinds from Artificial Intelligence, we believe the market has efficiently priced this optimistic scenario.", "The current valuation offers a risk/reward profile that is insufficiently skewed in our favor and fails to meet our firm's minimum 15% IRR hurdle for new long positions.", "The strategic pivot to data center revenue, now over 50% of the total, and its leadership in power-efficient HBM3E have structurally improved the business."], "published_at": null, "publisher": "tickertothesis.com", "search_query": "MU downside risk competition margin valuation guidance concern latest", "search_rank": 1, "search_snippet": "The significant, asymmetric downside risks associated with Samsung's competitive re-entry and the speculative nature of AI capex are not adequately compensated at this valuation.", "search_stage": "search_query_3_risk", "source_class": "web", "source_record_id": "source_13687c0a61cce873", "started_at": "2026-06-29T08:37:16.271740+00:00", "status_code": 200, "title": "$MU: Passing on a Fairly Valued Supercycle with Asymmetric Downside", "url": "https://tickertothesis.com/mu-investment-memo-2026-02-05/"}, {"access_status": "ok", "as_of": "2026-06-29T08:37:00.140519+00:00", "canonical_url": "https://www.capitalsight.net/2026/04/micron-technology-mu-deep-dive.html", "completed_at": "2026-06-29T08:37:17.466911+00:00", "content_hash": "42d6a9b43a3be5025c9b73e8f32f8b707c931afeee62c4b4337353e345b3df96", "content_type": "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "error": null, "ok": true, "paragraphs": ["Micron’s AI Memory Upcycle Is Strong, but Valuation Depends on DRAM Pricing Discipline Skip to main content Capital Sight Search Search This Blog Micron’s AI Memory Upcycle Is Strong, but Valuation Depends on DRAM Pricing Discipline on April 09, 2026 Get link Facebook X Pinterest Email Other Apps Executive Summary: Micron Technology is currently experiencing an unprecedented cyclical upswing, propelled by severe supply constraints and insatiable demand for High-Bandwidth Memory (HBM) infrastructure to support artificial intelligence workloads.", "With dynamic random-access memory (DRAM) and NAND flash prices surging to astonishing levels—up 140% and 170% year-over-year, respectively—near-term earnings power is poised to shatter historical ceilings.", "However, underlying the breathtaking top-line forecasts is a capital-intensive, high-fixed-cost commodity business with no durable economic moat, meaning investors must critically evaluate exit strategies before the inevitable supply glut strikes toward the end of the decade.", "The current windfall 